The '''Seram honeyeater''' ('''''Lichmera monticola''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Meliphagidae]].
It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Indonesia]], where it occurs on [[Seram Island|Seram]] in the southern [[Maluku Islands]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s.

